This topic describes how to determine if your existing deployment of File
Integrity Monitoring Add-on for PCF (FIM Add-on) can run on product tiles that
require Xenial stemcells.

This topic also explains how to update your FIM Add-on if it does not support product tiles that need Xenial stemcells.

Follow the instructions on this page if you are running the FIM Add-on and product tiles that require the Xenial stemcell.

##<a id="background"></a> Background

Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) products and tiles that are released after July 2018 require Ubuntu Xenial stemcells instead of Ubuntu Trusty stemcells.

Only recent versions of the FIM Add-on and ClamAV Add-on for PCF run correctly on Xenial stemcell-based VMs. 

## <a id="which"></a> Product Tiles that Use Xenial Stemcells

The following product tiles require the Xenial stemcell:

* PCF Event Alerts v1.2.2 and later

* Redis for PCF v1.14 and later

