##<a id="add"></a> Add the Xenial Stemcell Property to the FIM Add-on

If you are running the FIM Add-on v1.2.22 or v1.2.23 without the stemcell
property in the `fim.yml`, then you need to add the stemcell properties to your
existing `fim.yml` and redeploy.  Follow this steps:

1. SSH in to the Ops Manager VM.
   For how to do this, see [SSH into Ops Manager](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/customizing/trouble-advanced.html#ssh).

2. To retrieve and save FIM add-on runtime config, run the following command:

    ```
    bosh -e BOSH-ENVIRONMENT runtime-config –name fim > /tmp/fim.yml
    ```

    Where `BOSH-ENVIRONMENT` is the alias you set for the BOSH Director.

    For example:

    <pre class="terminal">$ bosh2 -e my-env runtime-config –name fim > /tmp/fim.yml </pre> 


3. Edit the `fim.yml` file adding or editing the lines from `include` to
   `- os: ubuntu-xenial` after `properties: {}` as shown below.


    ```
    addons:
    - name: fim
      jobs:
      - name: fim
        release: fim
        properties: {}
      include:
        stemcell:
        - os: ubuntu-trusty
        - os: ubuntu-xenial
    ```

4. To update the runtime config, run the following command:

    ```
    bosh2 -e BOSH-ENVIRONMENT update-runtime-config --name=fim /tmp/fim.yml
    ```

    For example:

    <pre class="terminal">bosh2 -e my-env update-runtime-config --name=fim /tmp/fim.yml</pre> 

5. Navigate to the Installation Dashboard in Ops Manager.

6. Click **Apply Changes**.

